text: So I know what this is and I know what it can do. I think we have to be extremely careful because I don't think anything is exactly what. What the algorithm or the materials say it is. For humans in terms of the laws of biochemistry, and I don't think it's true for machines because of the formal limitations of the algorithms that they're supposedly running. That's it. content_summary: The speaker discusses the limitations of both biochemistry in humans and algorithms in machines, suggesting that neither are fully defined by their supposed parameters. The speaker also mentions the involvement of postdocs, students, and collaborators in their research, and discloses involvement with three companies.
